 High School Diploma or equivalent with two (2) years of experience working with children, preferably children with disabilities, and demonstrate highly qualified status; or AA degree with 1 year of experience working with children preferably children with disabilities 
 Previous experience working with special needs students, students with communication disabilities, or students with Autism is preferred 
 Proficient computer/keyboarding skills including Microsoft Office Suite, particularly Microsoft Excel 
